<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1016" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1016">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Woodford</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-17"><hi rend="italic">February 17,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Spanish chargé has presented telegraphic message of condolence from His
                            Majesty’s Government. Convey deep appreciation of this tribute to the
                            memory of the many who perished in the destruction of the <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi>, and of this manifestation of sympathy with
                            the American people in their grief.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Day</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>